forget that I am a hard businessman and therefore above these... unnecessary emotions. True, I want to save you, but I also want money for it. You would have to pay me two thousand kruns.'

'It is not much,' said Krug.

'Anyway,' said Quist dryly, 'it is sufficient to pay the brave men who take my shivering clients across the border.'

